        "content": "<p>Microsoft has stopped making accessories in general as of last year, including the sculp keyboard which I've been using for over a decade. There's <a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/5/24026323/microsoft-incase-partnership-keyboards-accessories-partnership\">rumors that they will be back</a>, but in the meantime I've found the Logitech k860 and their vertical mouse to be a reasonable substitute.</p>\n<div class=\"message_embed\"><a class=\"message_embed_image\" href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/5/24026323/microsoft-incase-partnership-keyboards-accessories-partnership\" style=\"background-image: url(&quot;https://uploads.zulipusercontent.&quot;)\"></a><div class=\"data-container\"><div class=\"message_embed_title\"><a href=\"https://www.theverge.com/2024/1/5/24026323/microsoft-incase-partnership-keyboards-accessories-partnership\" title=\"Microsoft’s keyboards and mice will live on under a unique new partnership\">Microsoft’s keyboards and mice will live on under a unique new partnership</a></div><div class=\"message_embed_description\">Incase has stepped in to save Microsoft’s PC accessories.</div></div></div>",
